



Passy, Sunday Morning Augt. 2d 1778



Captain Jones begs the Commissioners to oblige him with Copies of the following lettersor with the liberty of taking Copies of Monseigneur De Sartines letter to the Commissioners respecting Captain Jones, of their Answer to that letter, of the Commissioners letter to Lieutenant Simpson in consequence of Captain Jones proposition in his favor, and of the paper dated the 4th of Julywhich being a memorandum of what Captain Jones had to communicate in conversation, he made out but one Copy.1
